headline: Accenture: Government Cuts Hit, But Core Strength Holds

headline: 2 Reasons to Like ACN and 1 to Stay Skeptical
summary: Over the past six months, Accenture’s stock price fell to $247.08. Shareholders have lost 19.7% of their capital, which is disappointing considering the S&P 500 has climbed by 21.3%. This might have investors contemplating their next move.
